â€¢	Press Win + R â†’ wf.msc
â€¢	Or use Control Panel â†’ Windows Defender Firewall â†’ Advanced Settings
2. List current firewall rules
â€¢	Go to Inbound Rules and Outbound Rules.
3. Add a rule to block inbound traffic (e.g., Telnet on port 23)
â€¢	Inbound Rules â†’ New Rule â†’ Port â†’ TCP â†’ Specific local port: 23 â†’ Block the connection
4. Test the rule
â€¢	Use telnet localhost 23 (will fail).
5. Add a rule to allow SSH (port 22)
â€¢	Inbound Rule â†’ New Rule â†’ Port â†’ TCP â†’ Specific local port: 22 â†’ Allow the connection
